Text.Value: Who killed you?
Are you really the strongest? Does that mean you are the boss?
Will you kiss my feet now?
Leave.
Absolute... is forever. She'll punish...

Text.Value: Will you kiss my feet again?
Of... course not. That's... disgusting...

EditorData.NodeContext: Very defensive. The player asked him if he had a thing for feet, but he denies it. He absolutely has a thing for feet.

Text.Value: Have you learned your lesson, now that you're dead?
So do you have a thing for feet, or...?
Do you have anything of value?
If I had... would've killed 'im...

Text.Value: No... not kissing you... anywhere...
The Absolute? Who is that?

Crusher. Strongest... of our tribe...

Text.Value: *The corpse does not stir. It will answer no more questions.*
*The corpse regards you lifelessly.*
Should be... boss. But Dror Ragzlin... hobgoblin.
Did you see a druid named Halsin?
Who are you?
*The spell's power wanes. You can ask no more questions.*
Toe ring... magic...
You... wait... Absolute... will make you pay...

Synopsis: SwD dialog for Crusher, an absolute legend (pun intended) among the goblin tribe.
